text.tspan: Using an object-oriented approach to deal with cross-cutting concerns
The obvious question is: Can we do that for services? And the answer is, of course:
Yes! Services do not need to be little monoliths. Services can, instead, be designed
using the SOLID principles, and given a component structure so that new components
can be added to them without changing the existing components within the service.
